      <Content>MT HOTTP-B NJPS מַחֲרֵשָׁתֹו | LXX RSV NIV NJB REB NRSV REB GNT CEV חרמשׂו = {L:חֶרְמֵשׂ&lt;SDBH:חֶרְמֵשׂ&gt;} "sickle, scythe". 'Ploughshare' is the traditional translation, but not adequate. Triangular blade does seem to be correct. Options to handle the (odd) repetition of 'plougpoint' in 1SAM13:20. (1) Emendation cf. versiones; (2) Follow vocalisation Masoretes, imlpying different object (3) Or part of the totality of plough.</Content>
    </Note>
  </Notes>
  <ContributorNote>In relation to "bronze or iron" and "plough(-point)": 6. Exegesis 6.1 Literal use, A.2, pp. 6-7; 6.4 Archeology A.1, pp. 10-11; 7. Conclusion, p. 11. </ContributorNote>
